    "updated_at": "2017-08-09T09:51:20Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hmm. I'm still not sure that it's a good idea to write anything to the console by default, even when there's an error. If users are writing console apps which handle exceptions but expect to be writing console output in a particular format, this will break them.\r\n\r\nWe could make it easier to opt in by adding a `UseConsoleLogging()` method though.\r\n\r\n(To be clear, I'm still fine with the rest of the changes here.)"
  },
